<p>
  Both Webpack and Vite handle CSS minification automatically in production builds (<code>mode: 'production'</code> or <code>vite build</code>). You generally don't need to configure anything — minification is on by default. The configuration above is only needed if you want to switch minifiers or add custom options.
</p>

<h2>Beyond Minification: Critical CSS and Async Loading</h2>

<p>
  The biggest CSS performance win isn't just minification — it's reducing render-blocking. The pattern is to extract the CSS needed for above-the-fold content ("critical CSS"), inline it in the <code>&lt;head&gt;</code>, and load the full stylesheet asynchronously:
</p>

<pre><code>{codeCritical}</code></pre>

<p>
  Tools like <code>critical</code> (npm package) can automate critical CSS extraction. Combined with minification, this eliminates render-blocking CSS entirely and significantly improves LCP scores.
</p>

